text: From notes. 12 oz bottle shared with Doug at his house on May 16. The pour is more of a mahogany color with a pretty decent clarity. There is a lighter tan head that falls quickly to a thin ring. The aroma is full of alcohol. There is a good coffee and chocolate behind that, almost like a decent mocha. There is a hint of barrel, but the whiskey just doesnt come through like I thought it would. The flavor is much of the same. Nice, distinct balances of coffee and chocolate with a light woodiness and a pretty strong whiskey toward the back end. This doesnt try to hide the alcohol at all. The mouth feel is lighter and clean with a soft carbonation and a lingeringly alcohol dominated finish. The chocolate and coffee do well, but they just need to take over the booze a bot. This was pretty decent.

12 oz bottle with an indecipherable industrial time stamp. Brown-black brew has an immediately disappearing head. Aroma is toasted walnut, espresso, soy, toffee and a touch of booze that seems more red wine than whiskey. Tastes of caramel, salty roasted peanut, milk chocolate and whiskey. Long finish has some prune, red wine, beef broth and toasted barrel. Medium-heavy body has low carbonation and a drinkable balance for such a big brew. Tastes like a very nice quadrupel.

Piana na 1cm, sycząca, po chwili pozostająca jedynie w formie firanki. Barwa ciemno brązowa, mętna. W aromacie przede wszystkim kawa i wanilia, w tle toffi, karmel, nalewka orzechowa - super! W smaku podobnie, słodkie, kawowe, karmelowe, melasowe, rodzynkowe, waniliowe... Goryczka nieduża, tytoniowo orzechowa, na finiszu whiskey, rozgrzewanie, likierowość. Niskie, drobne wysycenie, w odbiorze lepkie, lekko oleiste, średnio gęste.

Tradycyjnie już prawie genialne piwo z Prairie z małym zastrzeżeniem co do ciała, za to nieźle pijalne jak na 13% ABV! Chyba odrobinkę lepsze, bardziej złożone od Okie w wersji bez kawy.

Creamy and full bodied beer. Bourbon, coffee, roast, caramel, sweet fruits. Sweet with a light bitter finish. Very well balanced. 
Quite subtle. Very good.
Butelka. Mocny, intensywny aromat whisky, mokre drewno, fajne posmaki migdałów, orzechów laskowych w moim odczuciu. Bardzo przyjemne, lepkie, dlugie posmaki. Beczka wypracowala swoje.

Bottle. Pours clear chestnut, small beige head, good lacing. Aroma is whiskey, slightly stale coffee, hint of Bell pepper. Flavor is medium sweet, light bitter, whiskey, oak, coffee, ashtray, pepper. Medium body, creamy mouthfeel.
12 oz bottle, aroma is whiskey, caramel and coffee. Taste is coffee, cream, whiskey and oak. The coffee is a light to medium roast. Strong flavor but a much lighter roast than I prefer.
12oz bottle shared by Bvery, thanks buddy! Nice brown pour. Aroma of chocolate, whiskey, coffee. Taste follows, very well balanced. Usually dont like coffee but this is nice.
Bottle. Murky dark brown pour with a smaller head. Coffee, wood, whiskey - pretty boozy but quite good.

Bottle at home. Sweet, roasted taste of dried fruits, cookie dough, berries in alcohol, vanilla, cold coffee and hints of whisky. Slightly bitter aftertaste. Very nice and fresh taste of coffee. Medium/full bodied. Soft, smooth mouthfeel. Very balanced.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

UPDATED: FEB 23, 2017 Rami Rami is drinking a Coffee Okie by Prairie Artisan Ales at Saska KępaAromat 5/5. Figi kandyzowane, wanilia, rodzynki, susz, chleb. Megaintensywnie. Bosko. Smak gorzej, niemalo alko, ale nadal sups. Ciala srednioOcena potraktowana skryptem do przeliczania ocen (uzgodnienie UT/RB).
Superb beer with a fantastic mix of malty sweetness, warming alcohol, tart and spice, wood and light sourness.
Dark brown with almost no head. Sweet aroma with coffee notes. Strong sweetness with a touch of sour and coffee notes followed by quite strong bitterness. Hint of coffee bitterness in the aftertaste.
A very nice coffee beer. Pours dark brown, thick coffee and malty sweet beer. Nutty finish, some dirt and chocolate.

Draught. Dark brown coloured. Dense beige head. Aroma. Ripe fruits, caramel, coffee, light smoke, sweetness. Flavour. Sweet and ripe fruits, alcohol, dense coffee, light smoke, spice. Medium to full bodied. Ends fruity and sweet. Quite alcoholdense and warming.
Bottle at tasting. Aroma of strong coffee, booze, cream and chocolate. Taste has creamy coffee, oak, hazelnut, vanilla, some malt and a long sweet finish. Very nice.

Kolor:  Ciemnobrunatny. Piwo jest słabo przejrzyste. 
 Piana: Kurde... Słabiuteńka. Ciemnokremowa, drobno oczkowa, nietrwała.
Szybko opadła do chmurki, a ta wkrótce do zera.
Na krawędziach Sniftera z trudem można odnaleźć punktowe kropeczki. 
 Zapach: Móglbym się nim narkotyzować dzień i noc. Tyle akcentów bourbonu w tak małym bączku. Intensywne nuty dębowej beczki, whisky, szlachetnego alkoholu, wzbogacone o nuty kokosowe i waniliowe.
Chyba w żadnym piwie nie będącym Imperialnym Stoutem nie czułem takiej intensywności tej beczki.
Pod spodem przykryte są nuty czekolady, kakao i odrobinę włoskich orzechów.
Kawy jest w aromacie niewiele, ale nie jest to dla mnie żaden problem. 
 Smak:  Po pierwszym łyku już wiem, że to jest Sztos!
Piwo jest tak gładkie, tak aksamitne na języku.
Beczkowa strona trunku jest bardzo wyraźna. Każda, nawet słabo zaznajomiona osoba w temacie piwa, bez najmniejszego trudu rozpozna tutaj akcenty whisky i bourbonu.
A jest ich tutaj ogrom! Podbija je posmak zbutwiałego, mokrego drewna i dużo wanilii i kokosu. Ten drugi jest tak wyraźny, że mam wrażenie, jakby ktoś mi Bounty rozpuścił w piwie. Jeszcze nigdy nie czułem tak mocnego kokosa.
Piwo bazowe pokozuje takie składowe jak: belgijska czekolada, orzechy włoskie, karmel, cukier trzcinowy.
Kawa jest raczej w typie słodkiego caffee latte. Mogłaby być bardziej wyraźna.
13% alkoholu? To musi być jakiś żart? Pomyłka! Nie może być!
W ślepym teście postawił bym na 7-8% obj.
Tekstura piwa jest bajeczna, jedwabista.
Piwo jest pełne w smaku, wykleja usta i podniebienie. Aftertaste jest długi, przyjemny, gładki.
Fenomenalne na skale światową! 
 Wysycenie.  Minimalne. Praktycznie zerowe. 
 Podsumowanie:  

Piłem już wiele piw leżakowanych w beczce po bourbonie.
Były to najczęściej RIS-y.
Tutaj beczka zrobiła takie spustoszenie, że chwilami zaburza nawet piwo bazowe.
Tak potężnego kokosu nie czułem w żadnym piwie.
Taka gładkość na języku, kremowość, jedwabiste odczucie w ustach.
Niespotykane na taką skalę.
Piwo rozpływa się w ustach, jak najlepsze belgijskie pralinki.
Kawa w aromacie jest słabo wyczuwalna, ale w smaku już robi robotę. Ma ona słodki posmak, jak caffee latte z odrobiną mleka.

Piwo zapamiętam na bardzo długo. Między innymi za najbardziej dominującą beczkę w piwie-nie-będącym-RIS-em.
Boskie! Fenomenalne! Jedyne w swoim rodzaju!

Bottle at home from Saveur-Biere.com - Color: deep dark black beer with no carbonation and small brown head. Smell: coffee and roasted malt and black bread with caramel notes. Taste: full body with roasted malt and coffee domination, mocha, good attenuation. Aftertaste: coffee, sweet caramel and dark fruits, roasted malt. Good balanced. Alcohol.

Bottle @ home. Aroma of vanilla, oak, coffee, caramel. Clear dark brown with tan head, none lasting. Taste is moderate+ sweet, alcohol sweetness, light boozy and light+ bitter. Full body, oily feel and whisky sweet finish.

Bottle in the living room.
Pours a dark brown with a small but well retained head. 

The aroma is sweet & oaky... plenty of bourbon & vanilla... the coffee is mild but works nicely with the sweet malt, nuttiness, & toasty character. 

The beer is sweet, coffee & bourbon forward with some mild bitterness & vanilla. Its boozy but not terribly so. Pretty rich & great I suppose.

Draught @ CBC 2016 [ Green Session ]. - Copenhagen Beer Celebration 2016, Oksnehallen Vesterbro, Halmtorvet 11, 1700 Copenhagen, Denmark. [ As Prairie Coffee Okie ].Clear medium brown color with a average, frothy, good lacing, mostly lasting, off-white head. Aroma is moderate to heavy malty, dark malt, coffee, dusty coffee, rich coffee. Flavor is moderate to heavy sweet and bitter with a long duration, coffee, dark malt, sweet malt, alcohol. Body is medium, texture is oily, carbonation is soft. [20160514]

Bottle. Heavy malt aromas of roasted, dark bread and caramel, light cooked orange for the hops, light to moderate dough for the yeast, with coffee, toffee, prune, brown sugar, and sherry in the background. Head is small, fizzy/frothy, beige with spotty and slippery lacing and is mostly diminishing. Color is clear dark brown. Flavor starts moderately to heavily sweet and lightly acidic, then finishes moderately sweet and lightly bitter. Palate is medium to full, oily, with a soft carbonation and a moderately alcoholic finish. Lots of deep rich flavors and aromas in this American Strong Ale.
Shared from bottle at deansos. Black with off white head. Sweet malts. Big coffee, dry barley malt. Medium sweet and bitter.

35cl bottle shared.
No head. Deep burgundy pour. Lots of coffee. Very good

Bottle shared thanks to sjogro. Clear mahogany with beige head. Lots of fresh coffee beans, vanilla, toffee, caramel, light spices, green chilies, light cocoa. Lots of very fresh coffee beans here. Over medium sweet and under medium bitter. Over medium bodied. Very nice.

(330ml bottle from boxbeers.dk) Pours very deep brown with a small tan head that leaves a ring and lace. Aroma is very heavy on coffee beans with a vegetal/green pepper note, backed by raw sugar, dark caramel, nuts, oak, and light vanilla. Flavour is quite sweet compared to the nose with brown sugar and caramel in full force along with raisings, but still quite heavy on coffee beans, moderate roast, nutty, vanilla, whiskey. Remains quite sweet into the finish but a bit more bitterness helps dry things. Finish has coffee beans, earthy wood, slightly herbal, with a bit of alcohol heat. Smooth medium-full body is sticky and syrupy with low carbonation. Coffee addition really drives the nose but the base beer comes into play more on the tongue. Indulgent, slow post dinner sipper.
Coffee and whiskey and nutty, oh my! A sipper for sure but oh so smooth. A shade too sweet for my taste - fortunately was drinking it for dessert anyway.
Tap @ BRUS, Copenhagen 20161001. Roasted malty, coffee, vanilla, whisky, sweet, medium body with an oily texture. The finish is dry, roasted, sweet and alcoholic.
Tap @ Brus, Copenhagen 1/10-16. A lot of coffee beans/grounds with nutty notes, also woody and sweet. Body is medium, sweet finish with coffee beans/grounds and some warming alcohol.
Tap @ brus copenhagen. Pours a brown colour beer with a small head. Coffee with notes of toffee and roasted malts. Dry finish

Bottle. Color is dark brown to black. Head is thin and beige. Body is medium. Taste is medium sweet and medium bitter. Finish is long and medium dry. Aroma is chocolate, coffee, honey, caramel, raisins, pepper.

Bottle. Teku. Dark brown with medium, densed, light brown head. Good head retention and lacing. Nose is moderately to high in coffee aromas, also some woody and nutty character with whiskey/vanilla notes. But apart this there are strong caramel and brown sugar notes, along with some dark, very ripped fruits. Taste is semi-sweet to sweet, with lots of caramel/brown sugar-like flavors. Taste is constant thru the whole of degustation. Full body, oily and thick texture, rather soft carbonation, finish is sweet, roasted and coffee. Light to moderate ABV warming. In general if you like sweet, complex and malty beers with quite strong coffee notes go for it. This beer is interesting and deserves high rate, but Id prefer old school mikkeller beers based on coffee flavors and aromas.

Kávéval dúsított főzet ez is, a fekete ital kidomborodó karaktere mögött azonban ez esetben méltó tartalom áll, kifogástalan kombináció testet öltése, az alap verzió magasabb szintre helyezése: jól eltalált módon emeli a tétet az oklahomai főzde. Hideg gourmet kávé juharsziruppal, marcipánnal, barnacukorral, már ami az aromákat illeti, majd a tagadhatatlan american strong ale vonások az ízében is megmutatkoznak, a kávés, étcsokoládés, földes, egyszersmind tölgyes, vaníliás, tejszínes, egyszóval whisky-s jegyek mennyei kompozíciót alkotnak. Az efféle nagy formátumú sörök esetében nálam kedvezőbb fogadtatásra találnak az ízesítésre szánt jegyek, mint amilyen a kávé hangulata is, az önmagában is nagyszerű karakter hozzáértő kezek általi rafinéria hozzáadásával valóban felértékelődik.

Hazy dark brown with a fine light tan head. Aromas of roasted malts, chocolate, vanilla fudge, coffee and a light herbal tocuh develop. Just enough carbonation, mouthcoating smooth with a round and full body. Sweet borubon action with a light herbal bitter touch which opens up the beer. Lasting finish.

Aromat: nie jest tak zdominowany przez whisky, jak w wersji podstawowej. Głownie dzięki kawie. Na początku mamy znowu nuty beczkowe (whisky z wanilią), następnie karmel, ale kawa odzywa się równie szybko. Choć i alkoholowość wzrasta. Następnie czekolada, orzech, melano. Trochę za mało na 10.

Wygląd: barwa jest nieco ciemniejsza od wersji podstawowej i bardziej zamglona. Piana niestety jest niższa i mniej trwała, ale przy zwiększonej mocy można to wybaczyć.

Smak: i tu też mamy zmianę. Słodycz już tak nie dominuje, choć nadal jest znaczna. Całość jest znacznie bardziej złożona z karmelem, zbożem, chlebem, marcepanem, kawą, wanilią. Alkohol także mocniejszy. Wpływ beczki nieco mniejszy, ale to na korzyść. Goryczka niewielka, adekwatna. Tęga pełnia, niskie wysycenie i słodowo, kawowy finisz z nutą beczki i alkoholem wyraźnie (ale  w przyjemnym sensie) rozgrzewającym przełyk. Bardzo fajne piwo.

Sample @ CBC 16. Pours hazy brown with a beige head. aroma of coffee, cocoa, caramel, dry nuts and wood. The taste is coffee forward with notes of caramel roasted malts, cocoa and dry nuts. Pretty awesome!

Svart med ett gult skum. Alltid bra grejer! Fyllig doft och smak. Bra balanserad med kaffe och brända toner. God

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

CBC 2016 Green session. Dark brown body with a medium brown head. Dark fruity aroma with mild coffee, nuts and sweet bourbon. Taste is wood with lots of coffee, vanilla, toffee and plums. Mild alcohol warm finish, with a burned chocolate cake and roast aftertaste. Exceptional!

Bottle. Hazy chestnut brown with a small diminishing tan head. Nose has lots of coffee, wood, soil, nuts. Flavour is sweet with sugar, whisky, alcohol, syrup, coffee in the finish, wood. Full body, oily/sticky texture, heavy sweet, some bitterness. Sticky whisky booze.
Bottle @ two man strong one ill man lost in Germany. Dark brown body with a small offwhite head. Cold coffee, whiskey, roasted malt, vanilla, oak.
Bottle @ two men strong- one ill - lost in Germany. All of a sudden appearing. Pours Dark Brown with a creamy head. Coffee, Wood, caramel and a whiff of alcohol. Slick and vinouss. Smooth..
Bottle. Pours a dark brown. Aroma and taste are lots of whiskey, coffee, and some sweetness.
Draught at Mikkeller&Friends. Clear dark brown - offwhite head. Lovely coffee aroma and taste. Coconut. Chocolate. Bounty. Roasted. Sweet notes. Nice.
On tap @ Fermentoren. Cloudy brown with a tiny off white head. Fruity and oak tones. Fruit, oak, malt and hops. Full body with a long bitter / spicy finish.

Tap at Gollem. Pours very dark Brown. Smell is super-intense coffee. Some biscuit as well. Taste is full, coffee. Very gentle, intense on the coffee, but really mellow, not to Sharp. Vanilla. Very creamy. Not bad at all, even though the scent made me fear.

13%ABV. American Strong Ale.

Poured out brown. 29ºSRM.

Nose is full of sweet candy nose that youd expect with a quad/abt with the extra smoky kick of an espresso roast. The smoke in the nose becomes more aggressive and even takes on the character of lightly smoked peat with smoke and earth. The nose at the end even has some fresh spicy notes.

Mouthfeel is syrupy. Palate is rounded with a broad based and gentle sour, like the sour in brown sugar. Other flavors are that of the sour of a freshly pulled espresso. The espresso impression continues into the finish which is flowery with light citrus.

Overall, the experience is like enjoying a great single origin espressor from Ethiopia, maybe a Yergachef.

Goes on Favorites List !

Draught at Beers & Burgers, Gollem, Antwerp. Black beer with a nice beige head. Malty whisky aroma, caramel, vanilla, wood, coffee, raisins, dark chocolate, ice coffee, licorice notes. Coffee and wood flavor, raisins, figs, whisky, ash notes, caramel, some warming alcohol. Balanced and very full bodied. Really good.

Bottle at Gollem, Antwerp. BA strong brown ale with coffee beans, this cant go wrong... Sticky, pale greyish beige, moussy head, very dark chestnut brown robe with burgundy hue. Strong, fascinating and delicious aroma of candied cherry, vanilla-like oak, coffee grounds, tawny port, toffee, sugared milk, molasses, cola, blackberry. Sweet candied cherry and date onset, some candi sugar sweetness but nothing cloying and perfectly balanced with a dryness from the wood which increases towards the finish; softish carbo, caramelly malt sweet backbone with nutty edges, retronasal vanilla tannins, vinous ending with port-like effect, warming alcohol, complex. What a beauty...
Fad. Sort let olieret nærmest importør stout agtig. Ekstrem kaffe og en super dessert øl. En god del vanille noter kan også anes. I det hele taget aftenens bedste øl. Meget lækker.

13th June 2016Brewdogs Sheps Bush. Keg. Clear deep amber beer, good pale tan head. Sweet smooth malts, creamy sweetness. Resinous fruits. Little fruity whisky. Earthy coffee - espresso. Smooth sweetish finish with dried fruits. Pretty intense, both on the tongue and the wallet.
Truly amazing. Lots of depth, smell and taste of plenty of coffee, sweetness, warming alcohol. Some caramel, perhaps, awesome.

Bottle from Boxbeers. Hazy dark brown with a small beige head. Aroma is sweet, malty, roasted malt, dark malts, coffee and vegetables. Flavor is very sweet and rather bitter. Dry and rather bitter finish with lots of warming alcohol. 180616

Keg at Craft Covent Garden. It pours clear deep brown with minimalvhead. The aroma is rich, big coffee character, dried fruits, fruit cake, booze, vanilla, wood and cocoa. The taste is rich, slick, warming alcohol, earthy roast, big coffee notes, toffee, molasses, whisky, vanilla, toasted coconut with a warming toffee finish. Full body and limited carbonation. Plenty of coffee action. Nice, but could be done with more carbonation to make it more drinkable. Good fun.

250 ml. draft @ Gollem. Very dark brown with a small tanned head. Nose is overly roasted, harh roast & some burned coffee combined with very thick molasses & malt syrup, extreme molasses sweetness in the back. Taste is weird burned coffee, huge roast, very burned coffee leading into massive molasses & malt syrup, molasses sweetness is truly excessive, some lactose. Pure molasses & syrup body. A bit too unbalanced for me with overly roasted / burned coffee & extremely sweet and massive molasses notes. Not bad still but a bit too much in wrong directions for me, it just seems to me that I will never learn to love Prairie as much others seem to.
Unbelievable this is only rated a 99. Pours like an imperial brown but little coffee notes. This is by far the best coffee beer Ive ever seen. Fantastic beer!
Rated from notes taken 29 Mar 2016 -- Disappointed I dont taste more coffee, but this is still very good. Barrel is just apparent enough to not take away from the brown.
pour dark brown with a frothy off white head. light nutty, coffee, and whisky notes. taste light bitter, light sweet- full bodied average carbonation.
Pours deep dark brown with thin white head that quickly disappears. Nose is coffee. Aromas are toasted malts, caramel, coffee, spicy notes. Low carbonation, full body. Long sweet and whiskey.

Bottled 33cl. Color : dark brown ale with thin brown head. Nose : strong aromas of roasted malts, coffee and slight red pepper. Medium texture, low carbonation. Aromas : coffee, alcohol, roasted malt, toffee, spices and pepper . Low bitterness.

Sirupeuse & Acide & Alcooleuse & "peu de bulles" & Vanillée & crémeuse en bouche & " Des Notes dalcool de grain, boisée" & Cest plus équilibré lorsque ça se réchauffe. Donc en gros, cest une arme massive pas désagréable même plutôt sympathique mais est-ce vraiment essentiel ? Je préfère sans doute des notes plus rondes et moins acides dans ce genre de bière très alcoolisées

Draught. Creamy white good mostly lasting head. Black colour. Moderate malty and hoppy light sour nice aroma. JHeavy bitter powerfull flavor. Coffee, whisky and chocolate notes. Long heavy bitter finish. Creamy palate.

Tap @ Mikkeller Bar Aarhus. Pours hazy dark reddish brown with a small offwhite head. Aromas of whiskey, booze, coffee, dark fruits, plums, malt, caramel. Taste is vanilla, fudge, dark fruits, heavy whiskey, coffee, malt, spice, chocolate.

Toasted malts, chocolate, very sweet coffee, alcohol. Hazy, dark brown, small, creamy, beige head. Medium sweet. Coffee is immediately back, molasses, caramel, toasted malts, oak barrels, alcohol. Very nice ASA, very sweet coffee in aroma and palate. Keg at Craft Beer Co, Covent Garden.

Keg at Craft Covent Garden. Brown and hazy with very little head. Powerful aroma of roasted malts, nasty US coffee and creamy chocolate - not promising. But gets far more promising - low carbonation, rich, velvety and viscous - its sweet, but not excessively so. Rich, malty, vanilla, chocolate and coffee give way to a long warming alcohol finish. Good, not great
Bottle at Cotteridge Wines tasting room; hazy dark chestnut brown pour with a bubbly tan head, aroma has big coffee and dark fruits, taste has rich coffee, heavy bourbon, sweet fruits, quite chewy.

355 ml bottle.
Pours dark ruby red color with a small head. Aroma is quite strong with whiskey and coffee roast, malts, quite woody too, mild nuts on the background. Flavor is coffee and toasted malts, mild toffee sweetness and some whiskey tones, alcohol warms a bit as expected. Quite smooth palate, wooden tingliness on the aftertaste. Coffee fits here nicely and feels still fresh, not that much Brown Ale elements though. A very pleasant, especially aroma-vise, slow sipper. Excellent.
4426

Bottle. Very dark clear brown color, coaxed tan head. Aroma of brownies dipped in coffee, vanilla. Taste is burnt espresso, vanilla, toasted coconut. Retains its body. A big beer, but very tasty. A beer up front, with both the barrel and the coffee playing strong supporting roles.

Dark black with a centimeter of head. Strong coffee bean aroma. Thick brew dominated by coffee and a light syrupy sweetness (vanilla?). The coffee is really all I can taste, I hope as it warms up itll open up a bit. Maybe the syrupy sweetness is a bit whisky flavored.. Was expecting more than just a coffee beer with this one. Nice and strong but pretty one dimensional in flavor.

Bottle, 13%. Unclear dark brown with small off-white head. Aroma is Aroma is malt, caramel, coffee, bourbon, vanilla, vegetable, chili, chocolate, wood and nut. Flavour is malt, caramel, sweet, bourbon, wood, vanilla, toffee, little chili and medium bitter.

May 27, 2016. Bottle at home. 
Murky brown with a small tan head. Aroma is roasted coffee with coffee ground notes, caramel, whiskey, notes of prunes, figs, light green pepper notes. Taste is sweet, malty, light warming, light bitter. Finish is quite whiskey forward with warming notes alcohol notes along with coffee grounds, a touch of green pepper, sweet caramel, figs and vanilla. Medium bodied, soft carbonation. 
A bit too whiskey forward and the coffee has faded, still good!

W aromacie czekolada, orzechy laskowe, nutella, kawa, lekkie wtręty whisky, drewno, o to chodzi. W smaku o dziwo bardziej wytrawne niż sugerował aromat, ponownie nutella, choć jest jeszcze więcej kakao, kawy, obecne są niuanse beczki po whisky, także w nieco rozgrzewającym przełyk finiszu. Super, zwłaszcza aromat! Happy birthday to me! :D

Pours a very dark brown, almost black with a low tan head. Aromas of dark roasted coffee, brown sugar, chocolate, caramel, roasted nuts. Taste is malty and sweet with prominent bitter coffee notes. Mouthfeel is medium bodied with low carbonation.

Sample at CBC 2016. 

Black with a small tan head. Aroma and taste of coffee, roasted malt, some vanilla and chocolate. The body was full and the finish with warming alcohol. Tasty.

Pours dark brown, almost black color, clear, might be brilliant, with light brown or beige tan head. Aroma: intense malt aroma, supported with coffee nibs, hint of whiskey and dried chilli.
Very similar are flavors: intense malt flavor, with notes of toffee, coffee, supported with whiskey, vanilla, coffee nibs, dried chilli, milk chocolate... Dried fruit like prunes...finish is sticky, dry. Body is medium, texture soft, carbonisation is low. Alcohol warmth is noticeable, but gentle.
Tap @CBC16. Cloudy dark brown, small tan creamy head. Roasted malt, coffee and nutty aroma. Sweet caramely and nutty flavour. Warming booze.
Tap at CBC 16. Hazy brown with a small tan head. Big coffee aroma with caramel, toffee, sweet malt and roast. Flavour is heavy sweet and moderate bitter. Above medium bodied with soft carbonation.
CBC2016. Trübes orange braunes Bier mit einer geringen beigen Schaumkrone. Geruch leicht röstmalzig, Kaffee. Geschmack süß malzig, Karamell, Kaffee, trocken.
12oz bottle pours a dark brown color with a bit of head. Rich coffee flavor, lots of whiskey. A little hot. But it all comes together to make a delicious brew.

Pours dark brown with low tanned head 
Aromas of whisky, oak, vanilla, dried fruits, fudge 
Taste has sweet notes of vanilla, fudge, brown sugar, hints of chilies

Tap @ CBC -16. dark brown with a small tan head. loads of coffee on the nose along with malts and a lightly roasted profile. taste is sweet with malts and caramel. some coffeee and roasted malts. really nice albeit sweet. full bodied with soft to avg co2
CBC. Dark chestnut with a small white head. Aroma of cold coffee, green pepper and toffee. Sweet malty flavour with loads of coffee. Notable alcohol in the finish.
Tap@ CBC 2016. Pours dark brown with a thin brown head. Strong coffee, roasted malt, ash, burntness. Flavor has similar things. Coffee dominates, but more like cold coffee.
Tap at CBC2016, Copenhagen. Colour is dark brown with small white head. Aromas and flavors: Dry fruits, coffee, sweetness and malts.
Tap @ Fermentoren, Aarhus. HAzy brownish pour with a small head. Tons of caramel, sweet cocoa, light coffee, syrup, chocolate milk, toffee and fudge. Delicious!

Draught at Mikkeller & Friends.
Clear ruby coloured with a small beige head.
Light roasted aroma of coffee and fresh ground coffee.
Sweet and fruity flavour of caramel and coffee.
Sweet finish.

bottle, bought from online web order. poured a deep brown to more black colour with a tanned head. nose of sweet roasted malts, licorice, sweet dark fruits, roasted coffee, chocolate, sweet syrup, oak, vinalla, an cognac barrel. bourbon taste, sticky, and full bodied. nice. improvement to the regular okie

Draught at Mikkeller Bar, Stefansgade. Pitch black with a thin tanned head. Roasted aroma with red berries , dark malts, liquorice whisky barrel. Taste is bitter-roasted. Full body with a oliy texture. Finishes dry and bitter roasted with soy sauce. Excellent, decent drop, this.

Aroma and taste is prominent roasted coffee, roasted malts, cocoa, mocha, roasted finish. Nice.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Draft @ Mikkeller & Friends, Copenhagen. Pours a black color with a small off-white head. Has a roasted malty woody coffee aroma. Roasted malty woody vanilla and coffee flavor with hints of chocolate. Has a roasted malty coffee woody vanilla and chocolate finish.

Tap. Deep brown body with a small off-white head. Aroma of coffee, wood, vanilla and woodey notes. Sweet flavor that ends up more dry with some alcohol. Medium bodied, oily texture and soft carbonation. An excellent Ale indeed. 🌟🌟🌟🌟

Draft. A red-brown beer with a tan head. The aroma has notes of roasted malt, milk chocolate, coffee, and a bit of alcohol. The flavor is sweet with notes of coffee, roasted malt, chocolate, whiskey, and alcohol, leading to a dry roasted finish.

On tap at Fermentoren Aarhus. Pours a clear, dark brown with a small, off white head. Aroma has huge bourbon, fruity iced coffee, lots of caramel, vanilla, dates, figs, toffee, light toasted malts, coconut. Smells really really good! Taste is super sweet up front with an almost citric sugar-sweetness, lots of caramel mid sip and then ends off with a dry bourbon character that binds together greatly with bitter and fruity acidic coffee. Sticky body and an average to low carbonation. Really tasty!

Draught @ Fermentoren, Aarhus. Pours very dark brown with a small offwhite head. Aroma of sweet malt, rich coffee, coffee grounds, expresso, wood, light vanilla, light bourbon. Flavor is light sweet, malty, rich coffee, expresso, bourbon, little vanilla, wood, alcohol. Full body, average carbonation, light sweet finish with warming alcohol. 010516
Tap @ Feementoren, Aarhus. Nice head with good duration. Color is black. Aroma and taste are rich coffee, caramel, nuts, roast malt, bourbon, vanilla, fruits and hops. Lovely and good drinkability.

From tap. Pours hazy dark brown to black with a small tan head. Aroma is roasted malty and coffee. Sweet and alcohol dense. Dark malty and rich coffee to chocolate. Dry and roasted finish. Smooth chocolate and alcohol finish.
Very dark brow pour with a modest beige head. Coffee, burnt caramel, figs, cherries, bourbon and a pinch of salt. Super smooth texture.

Dark brown color with tan head. Aroma has really nice bourbon and caramel with some coffee in the background. Taste starts slightly sweet with caramel notes, continues with bitter coffee and finishes with green coffee / hops. Medium to heavy body, sticky with light to medium carbonation. Really nice overall, I just wish the coffee was more intense.

At a tasting, small creamy beige head, deep brown color, strong aroma of coffee beans and cold brewed coffee with vanila, nuts and caramel, flavor of caramel, coffee and nuts and muddy hints, very sweet but not cloying, pairs perfectly with sweet chocolate. Excellent and mellow.

Aroma of bourbon, oak, vanilla, coffee, plums, nuts. 
Pours reddish black with a thin bubbly white head. 
Taste is medium plus sweet, medium bitter. The aroma transfers perfectly to the taste and has even more depth and complexity. No trace of alcohol.
Medium plus body, very smooth, soft carbonation, sweet finish but with a slight coffee edge behind. Crazily good brown ale.

(33 cl bottle in wine glass.) This is a phenomenal beer. 13 percent ABV is weighed up beautifully by a fat, oily malt profile and freshened with hops that really need to fight in order to push through the massively thick coffee foundation of this brew. Absolute world class.

Bottle 355ml @ Sommerhuset
Pours dark reddish brown with a few off-white bubbles. Aroma has notes of roasted malt, chocolate, cocoa, coffee, oak, alcohol and brown sutgar. Taste is medium to heavy sweet and light to medium bitter with a long warm, caramel, chocolate, cocoa, coffee and oak finish. Body is full, texture is oily, carbonation is flat.

Bottle. It pours a dark chestnut to brown body under a small, beige head. The aroma has a lot of lovely coffee, with a touch of alcohol and caramel. Some roasted malts, brown sugar and dark chocolate notes. Its full-bodied, warming and quite smooth on the palate, Brown sugar, molasses, some dark chocolate and loads of delicious coffee in the flavor, along with general sweetness, alcohol and some bitterness. Everlasting coffee dominated finish where some licorice and dark chocolate chimes in. Some roasted malts. Probably a bit heavy on the booze this one, but its a damn fine beer anyway. 160423
Aroma is coffee, malts and a hint of skunky/spices. The flavor is coffee, caramel/toffee, dark malts, mild dark fruit, fruit and a tart/acidic finish.

Bottle shared by Marcus. Aroma is incredibly coffee. Med + + body. Flavor is chocolate and coffee, yet not mocha. Lots of coffee, lots of dark malt, some chocolate. Heat is barely detectable. Great stuff.
Bottle from Capitol Beer & Tap Room. Pours dark brown with a transient tan head and a coffee and treacle aroma. There is a full-bodied dark molasses and coffee flavor with a strong whiskey finish.

Deep brown practically black with a few bubbles. Rich malts, sweet coffee, chocolate, heavy dough and caramel. You can eat this stuff with a spoon, chewy malts, sticky, alcohol, vanilla, wood, coffee (reminds me of bomb), and a sweet finish
Pours tan, minimal head. Bourbon in the nose. Taste has all the elements of oak and bourbon, solid black coffee. Light to medium body.

Bottle shared at a tasting at Maxs place. Dark brown with a beige head. Big aroma, a bit boozy, full of coffee beans, whiskey, vanilla, caramel, nuts. Powerful sweet flavor, with caramel, nuts, whiskey, vanilla, coffee, a bit of booziness. Rather full-bodied, rounded. Great stuff.
Aroma is like a Snickers bar. Chocolate, caramel, and a little nutty. Malt flavors really stand out but complimented by the oak, coffee, and whisky. Variety of taste and and pleasant finish.

A noticeable improvement on the good but a little hot okie. The coffee barrel combo is reminiscent of KBS, if a little more of a sipper. Less dark roast than any stout too, but the coffee barrel and sweet malt are nice together.

12 ounce bottle. Pours a dark brown color with a small white head. A big sweet balance of bourbon and coffee. The flavor is big vanilla, bourbon, sweet rich coffee, milky. Finishes with more coffee. Very rich. Very nice brew.

Bottle enjoyed by the fire. Pour is murky brown with a light brown head. Aroma is coffee and whiskey with brown sugar, vanilla, and a touch of maple. Flavor is rich toffee malt with a nice blend of coffee, maple, and vanilla. Alcohol well hidden. Really tasty.

Pours hazy deep brown, mahogany, with nearly flat light tan head. Aroma of coffee beans, vanilla, milk chocolate, butterscotch. Taste is very sweet, coffee and chocolate, rich butterscotch, some pepper, lingering boozy sweet finish. Medium bodied, sweet and smooth, with average carbonation.
Bottle from Craigs, dregs run. Pours hazy brown with a thin beige head. Aromas of vanilla, coffee beans, whiskey. Taste is boozy coffee. Hot finish.

Pours opaque chocolate brown with a fairly thick tan head. Aroma presents coffee, roast malt, peppery, woody and yeasty tones. Flavor roars quality coffee, roasted malt, chocolate, molasses and woody notes across the palate, along with hints of whisky and yeast - and an occasional peppery whisper. Mouthfeel features firm, viscous texture, if not a lot of fizz. This bold strong ale drinks like a stout and will please anybody who likes dark beers that burst with flavor.

Surprisingly clear Cola brown, nice fluff of an off white head. Nose is rich toffee, big big fresh percolated coffee. Rich vanilla sweet burn, soft spice. Carbonation is fairly stern and brassy mouthfeel. Finishes clean birstley sweet and some coffee tang, lingers creamy sweet. Surprisingly drinkable with a long drawn ABV.Bottle, Pig Out Tasting.
Bottle at craigs. Pours deep brown, nose is roasted coffee, vanilla, chocolate, taste is chewy caramel, toffee, vanilla, bourbon, coffee, sweet.
Bottle at home... Dark brown black... Thin tan lacing... Massive coffee roast malts.. Coffee nose... Dark chocolate... Bitter coffee. Dry dark coffee roast.. Massive coffee...
Pours brown with a slight light brown head. Aroma is coffee, garden peas, oak. Taste is coffee, raisins, chocolate sweet, vanilla, bourbon, molasses.

Mahogany pour with a light khaki frothy half inch of head falling to a solid ring and dots of lace and alcohol legs

Seamless integrations of medium roast coffee, creamy oak, coconut, and bourbon with accents of friendly, lightly spicy heat... fig, raisin, plumb nuances, cola... donuts?... maple long johns... syrup and pancakes... smooth, cohesive, creamy medium-plus body

Served at 55º in to Orrefors Difference Porter snifter
Pours dark brown with a tan head. Aroma is coffee, dark fruits, whiskey and brown sugar. Taste follows nose.
Bottle shared by Brian. Pours a mostly transparent brown. Aroma and taste of coffee, booze, vanilla, some chocolate.

12 oz bottle. Pours a dark murky brown with just a thin ring of a head. BIG aroma of coffee, toffee, and enough alcohol it is a bit tough to hang with it long enough to get anything else, but patience will be rewarded, like with a good bourbon. Caramel sweetness, with just a bit of bitterness from the coffee, and bread puddiing with whiskey sauce finish. Fantastic and dangerous at 13%

Pours a clear brown with a small off white head and little lacing. Whiskey is prominent in the smell along with some vegetal coffee and prune. Taste starts off with some caramel sweetness, then you get the whiskey flavors, some toasted malt and chocolate. Just a little coffee along with some vanilla and prune. Finishes with some sweetness and alcohol warmth. Body is light but feels more substantial because of the sweetness. Moderate carbonation. Reminded me of a Barleywine. Really enjoyed.
Bottle. The look is dark, beige colored, brownish color, cola. The smell is coffee, fresh coffee, whiskey, wood, rich, and good. The taste is alcohol, coffee, wood, whiskey, and good.
12 oz bottle. Dark brown with a small beige head. Aroma is of coffee, espresso, smoke, toast, oak. Taste is of whiskey, coffee, oak, cocoa, toffee, and light smoke.
Cloudy brown body. Whisky barrel is a little overdone but goes well with the coffee.

2/12/16. 12oz bottle from Craft on Draft. Dark brown pour under a small tan head, mild lacing. I had to pour high and strong to coax any head out of this and it was gone fast after. Just a small khaki ring. Barrel is subtle, some sweet fudgey notes, vanilla, mild coffee, loads of caramel. Sweet flavor with loads of caramel, chocolate, and fudge, hints of vanilla, barrel, relatively subtle coffee. This beer is a touch sweet for me at this moment at least. Thick and creamy.

Pours dark brown with an off white head that fades to a ring around the outside. Some faint bubbles coat the surface.

Whiskey and coffee in the aroma. 

Whiskey hits you with some subtle coffee in the flavor. Caramel-ish middle with a smooth whiskey finish. Not boozy at all. 13%abv is well hidden.

A little thin mouthfeel wise for my liking but its a brown not a stout so I understand. 

Pretty damn good beer. Interesting take on a brown ale.
Bottle pour at EBF. Dark pour with light head. Roasted coffee, whiskey, sweet aromas. Flavors were coffee and whiskey forward, roasted, sweet malts and oak tones.

Draft Extreme Beer Fest 2016. Aroma is light roasted coffee, oak, weak bourbon, English toffee, nuts. 
Flavor is cocoa powder, caramel candy, roasted grain. The bourbon doesnt slap you in the face to tell you it is here. The barrel aging is more just an oak character. The coffee is found in a mild nuance toward the finish. The most impressive thing here is the fact that the ABV is completely hidden. I think the brown ale base made this way lighter in body then it should be. I liked that the brewer tried to do something special with a brown ale. Unfortunately the body suffers a bit because of the base. Still very happy to have sampled it.

Aroma is coffee, boozy and oaky (a play on words?). The coffee is bitter and there may be too much oak in the scent. Dull black color with virtually no foam. Looks foreboding, you can see the ABV. Tastes sweet from the whiskey barrel, boozy with a coffee punch than is much less bitter than in the aroma. The whiskey comes through in the aftertaste, leaving a very slight booze burn. Very unique; I dont think I have ever had a BA Imperial brown ale. Palate is good for the style with some carbonation to remind you that its not a stout. I really liked this offering from Prairie.

poured a dark brown with a thin creamy beige ring on top. Nose is heavy coffee, chocolate, whiskey and rich malts. Medium mouthful. The whiskey comes through first followed by the coffee and chocolate with a hint of dark berries. Smooth with a bit of a bite although at 13% it is very drinkable.

Dark brown in color.... Aroma of coffee, chocolate malts, maple syrup, hint of rye whiskey... Flavor is sweet chocolate, syrup, lactose, body is surprisingly smooth and not overly rich but not too thin either, whiskey notes are totally subdued... Really nice 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Bottle to snifter (shared with the Mrs.). Looks good for the style; a translucent dark brown with light beige head that steadily dissipates into thin lacing. Smells malty with a strong coffee presence alongside notes of oak and a bit of vanilla. Some roast too. Tastes like it smells, but sweeter, with a slightly hot medium full-bodied mouthfeel. Some bitterness from the roast. Good, not great.

Bottle. Rich coffee aroma with notes of chocolate, whiskey and vanilla. Pours dark brown with a thin light brown head with OK retention and good lacing. Starts with rich chocolate and some coffee but not too much. Finishes smooth with more roasty coffee and whiskey and vanilla notes as well. Very good but I didn't like it as much as the original.
Holy fucken shit what a nose. Coffee and booze and amazing. Smells yum. Taste is slightly bitter cocoa and lactose sugary sweet. Pretty fucken good.
Mahogany pour with an off white that fades to a ring. Aroma is coffee, maple syrup, and whiskey. Taste follows the nose with some dark fruit and chocolate added in. On the sweet side. Slick palate.

pours a darkk murky burgundy. Aroma is sweet with lots of fresh brewed coffee, whisky and maple. Flavor is the same with a light note of tabacco.. Big alcohol in this one. Medium body. Sticky texture. Sweet bitter finish. Damn good!

12 ounce bottle into tulip glass, bottled on 12/2/2015. Pours clear nearly opaque dark brown color with a small dense light khaki head with good retention, that reduces to a spotty lace cap that lingers. Light spotty lacing clings around the glass. Aromas of huge nutty dark roasted coffee, chocolate, cocoa, caramel, toffee, brown sugar, toasted bread, vanilla, cream, oak, bourbon, light dark fruit, and oak/toasted earthiness. Fantastic aromas with awesome complexity, robustness, and balance of dark/bready malt, coffee, and bourbon barrel notes; with great strength. Some light booze appears in the aroma as it warms. Taste of huge nutty dark roasted coffee, chocolate, cocoa, caramel, toffee, brown sugar, toasted bread, vanilla, cream, oak, bourbon, light dark fruit, and oak/toasted earthiness. Light-moderate bourbon/oak spiciness and roasted coffee bitterness on the finish; with lingering notes of coffee, chocolate, cocoa, caramel, toffee, brown sugar, toasted bread, vanilla, cream, bourbon, oak, light dark fruit, and oak/toasted earthiness on the finish for a while. Fantastic complexity, robustness, and balance of dark/bready malt, coffee, and bourbon barrel flavors; with a great malt/bitter/spiciness balance and zero cloying flavors after the finish. Light carbonation and fairly full bodied; with a creamy and lightly sticky/chalky balanced mouthfeel that is nice. Alcohol is fairly well hidden with a light-moderate warmth lingering after the finish. Overall this is an incredible barrel aged imperial brown ale style. All around awesome complexity, robustness, and balance of dark/bready malt, coffee, and bourbon barrel flavors; and very smooth to sip on for the huge ABV. The coffee character is enormous in this beer, lending a lot of earthy/light fruity character; with a great balance of the dark malt and barrel notes. A highly enjoyable offering.
12-oz bottle from beertopia. chocolate coffee nose, huge chocolate, creamy, boozy. the best thing anybodys ever done with a brown ale.

12 oz. bottle. Deep brown. Very little by way of bubbles. Smell is brown sugar, coffee, and bourbon. Coffee gets stronger as it warms. Tastes of whiskey up front. Then caramel and nutty malts. Gets sweeter as it warms. Coffee is aggressive in the back end and cuts the sugars. Heavy and boozy. Took a while to work through this. A dessert beer in all respects, but a fine one at that.

Pours a dark brown with a very thin white head. Aroma is coffee, roast, oak, and toffee. Flavor is heavier on the oak, with coffee and caramel. Hides the alcohol very well. Has a smooth body. A very solid strong ale.

12oz bottle - pours a dark brown , heavy coffee and cream aroma . Huge coffee flavor with notes of vanilla and oak . Alcohol is well hidden . One of the best coffee beers I've had . 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

The smell is COFFEE BEANS!!! Everything else is almost non-existent. Coffee brown color, the taste is malty, sweet, almost syrup sweet, with huge coffee notes and a bitter taste after the swallow. I havent had a beer like it. The ABV is intense, but not much burn for a 13%. Hefty price for such a small bottle, I cant recommend it for the average drinker but if you love coffee beers and strong ales, you will enjoy this one.

Dark brown/cider color; Medium creamy body; Aroma of toasted sweet malt, oak, rich coffee beans, vanilla, & whiskey; Flavor of roasted sweet malt, caramel, molasses, rich coffee, some dark fruit notes, and whiskey; Warm/hot finish; Nicely balanced; Heavy on the coffee & pretty potent - I enjoyed it!

Craft Brewers, is there any beer style you wont infuse with coffee? Apparently not. And for that, you beautiful crazy bastards, I thank you. With Coffee Okie, Prairie has decided to put coffee in an... American Strong Ale? (Imperial) Brown Ale? I dunno. In any case, Coffee Okie gives you a noseful of fresh, fruity coffee roast. Theres also some oak, toasted malt, and sugary booze. Flavor has earthy woodsiness, caramel, and coffee. Prairie makes weird beers beautiful. Theyve sure done it with Coffee Okie.

Bottle. The pour is brown. The aroma is fantastic, rich coffee, subtle booze. The taste has nice coffee, but I get little whiskey. Good drinking, not great. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

UPDATED: JAN 2, 2016 Bottle.

A- Coffee, subtle whisky.

A- Mahogany color, hazy liquid, minimal head.

T- Coffee, oak.

P- Full body, average texture, average carbonation, mellow finish.

O- Not as big as I thought it could be In fact, at points the aroma and taste seemed a bit subdued. Not necessarily weak, but the coffee and whisky notes were pretty minimal. It was still really tasty though. In fact, it was damn good.
Bottle, pours ruby brown with small head. Lots of heat and warming qualities in the chest. Notes of fig, heavy whiskey, green coffee, vanilla, and barrel heat. Not bad but shes a strong girl.

Hyper expensive 12oz bottle@ trailer. Clear mahogany color with tan sheen. Big coffee ground aromas with sugar, light roast whiskey vanilla. Medium bodied with soft carbonation. Big whiskey vanilla, wet wood flavors with some drip coffee, light roasted nuts----warming boozy finish___tasty.
user_location: Same Trailer, Different Park, Louisiana, USA

text: Bottle shared with Paul and Brendan at The Well in Brooklyn, December 18th, 2015. Pours a pitch black body with no head. Nose is rich, beautiful coffee roast. Really delicious coffee aromas. Mouthfeel is medium to full bodied with notes of chocolate, coffee filters and rich espresso.

Medium dark, half finger off white head. Smells of earthy coffee, anise, vanilla, bourbon, dirt. Taste is sweet bourbon, earthy coffee, dirt, vanilla, anise. Fairly boozy and earthy, I don't like the coffee mixed with a brown as much as a stout but less intense would be better. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
12 ounce bottle. Carbonation quickly fades. Big coffee nose. Coffee and whiskey throughout. A bit boozy. But pretty nice.

Bottle. Pours near black with a tan head that dissipates to the edges. Aroma is full of coffee with a bit of bitter dark grains and a hint of whiskey underlying. Flavor has combines whiskey and coffee with a sweet dark grain backbone and a hint of roasted malts.

Aroma is booze, barrel, coffee, roasted malt, lots of oak. Appearance is dark brown, light brown head. Taste is a bunch of coffee, but mostly barrel, booze, very woody. Mouthfeel is medium body and medium carbonation. Overall, the taste disappoints but I bet this is good after it ages.

Bottle to glass. Pours a light brown, semi transparent. Aroma is coffee, cocoa, vanilla, whiskey. Taste is coffee, whiskey, oak, faint cocoa, a bit of sweet malts. Medium body and carbonation. Solid beer!

Pours black with a small light tan head that turns even lighter as it rings the top. Big roasted coffee aroma with notes of whiskey and oak. Taste is the same with hints of cocoa and banana. Smooth mouthfeel. Like to know what kind of whiskey barrels it was stored in and how long. (Not getting bourbon, guessing some other kind of whiskey).
12 ounce bottle. Pours a dark golden red with a decent beige head. Aroma of coffee, malt, and whiskey. Taste is coffee, malt, whiskey, caramel, and some dark fruit. Smooth and delicious.

The beer pours deep mahogany brown with a small tan head. The aroma has smooth child brewed coffee, rich toasty toffee and caramel malt, some vanilla and nuttiness. The body is huge and lush with some soft carbonation. The taste starts with rich coffee, walnuts, hazelnuts, toasty malt, vanilla, bourbon and oak. The finish has all of the elements blended beautifully and dark caramel along with some coconut. Fantastic beer.

12oz bottle split amongst the group during the poker part of the Spit Cup/2000th weekend. Thanks guys! Dark brown pour. Raw coffee grounds, chocolate in the nose. Taste is more chocolate, less coffee grounds. Alcohol, and light lactose. Solid. Very tasty for an impy brown. Finishes a bit rough and bitter (coffee ish). With alcohol. 13.8

bottle poured into a snifter..brown with a medium tan head..aroma of coffee and whiskey..tastes of coffee and a little whiskey..coffee flavor is so over the 
top that the actual beer taste is lost..really disappointing.
